This paper is about video action recognition using deep neural networks on mobile devices. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper focuses on visual data and uses deep learning techniques for action recognition. Other possible sub-categories include cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these fields are also relevant to the paper's topic.
